You're welcome everyone.

@memozozz - the presets I use (along with some basic instructions) are available for download:
http://www.peejeshare.com/files/362129257/HandBrake_Presets.zip.html

@flashfart - sorry, neither of those titles is likely within the next two month. But feel free to remind me in August in case you haven't found them elsewhere by then.

@Dalubai - If we're thinking of the same film (http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1899353/), when I spot a high-quality source, I'll def convert & up.

@memozozz - yeah, those times sound about right.

One piece of advice tho: if you're gonna go below 20, a better use of your time is using the Fast preset and cranking CQ to 18.

The Best presets are for those who want smaller files sizes and need HB to make more refined decisions (since you're using a lower bit rate); their usefulness is negated once you go below 20.
